I am recording this as baleatus litorisilva based on location, although patterns of lizards from this population often better match baleatus lineatacervix, which is nominally only from Isla Saona. Based on patterns seen in baleatus litorisilva in Punta Cana, as well as variation seen in del Este, I do not think these two subspecies are distinct (DLM 2019.08).
